Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a garlic press). Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and sliced). Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm chunks, peeled if you prefer). When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British beef mince{240} and sliced pepper. Cook until browned, ~{6-7%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef has browned, stir in the @Central American style spice mix{1} and half of the garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}, @beef stock paste{10} and @water{75}(for the beef). Bring to a boil then turn the heat down to a simmer. Cook until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, turn your #grill{} on to high. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{45}(grated). Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Mix through the cheese and spring onions then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm and set aside.

Transfer the beef filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Spread the mash over in an even layer. Grill until golden brown and piping hot, ~{5-6%minutes}. Wash out the (now empty) frying pan and put back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. When hot, add the @peas{120} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once everything is ready, serve the pie between your plates with the peas alongside. Enjoy!